'''Eduardo Gonzalez Via<U+00F1>a''' born [[November 13]], [[1941]]. Peruvian author and member of the Peruvian Academy of the Spanish Language. He was awarded the [[Juan Rulfo]] Award for best short stories in [[1999]] for the short piece "Siete Noches en California". His works include Los Peces Muertos (1964), Habla Sanmpedro: llama a los brujos (1979), El tiempo del amor (1984), El amor viene volando (1990), Sarita Colonia viene volando (1987), El correo de Salem (1999) and Los sue<U+00F1>os de Am<U+00E9>rica (2001).  Currently, he teaches Spanish language, literature and history at [[Western Oregon University]] in [[Monmouth, Oregon]].

